Introduction

I am working on sea otter whisker analysis over time from the root to the tip of the whisker. As my analysis is not complete, this is includes 20 sea otters as a population between Klawock and Naukati on Prince of Wales Island. Sea otter whiskers were collected from June 26- August 6, 2019.

Analysis

First, I want to load the correct programs and files. I am loading ggplot to print some nice graphs, and load the stable isotope whisker data. Otter ID should be read as a factor.

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

#load whisker data
whisker <- read.csv("whiskers.csv")
whisker$OtterID<-as.character(whisker$OtterID)

Data Cleaning

Otter 163532 has very odd values, while it is being re-run I have seperated out the values and am going to make the whisker file without this sea otter.

# for right now, I want to separate 163532 because it is an odd otter
oddotter<- filter(whisker, OtterID=="163532")
whisker<- filter(whisker, OtterID != "163532")
